        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Norden, or 14 miles northwest of Ainsworth, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ainsworth, Johnstown, Antelope Peak, and Bobcat State Wildlife
Management Area.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 183 between mile markers 196 and 199.
Highway 20 between mile markers 231 and 244.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
